    <description>Tomcat is a Application Server. It is possible to run Web application ARchive (WAR) files using Tomcat. Apache Tomcat requires a JDK in order to run.

### Optional installation commands:

`choco install teamcity-server -params "username=*user* password=*password*"` to specify a user account for the TeamCity service. This defaults to the SYSTEM account.

`choco install teamcity-server -params "username=*user* password=*password*"` domain=*domain*' to specify a domain user account for the TeamCity service. This defaults to the SYSTEM account.

`choco install teamcity-server -params "unzipLocation=*path*"` to specify the root directory for the tomcat service. This defaults to `C:\Program Files\Apache Software Foundation\Tomcat`.
Note: An apache-tomcat-7.0.59 folder is always created, so the actual install path is `C:\Program Files\Apache Software Foundation\Tomcat\apache-tomcat-7.0.59` for the default case or *path*\apache-tomcat-7.0.59 with a custom option.
    </description>
    <summary>Application Server. Windows 32 and 64 bit. Default install location: `C:\Program Files\Apache Software Foundation\tomcat\apache-tomcat-7.0.59`.</summary>
